nd cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/speed 2.5<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved green beans and cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Transfer to a bowl, allow to cool for 30 minutes then refrigerate until serving. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl."},{"content":"Preheat barbecue to medium heat."},{"content":"Remove chicken legs from bag, reserving piri piri marinade. Place chicken legs on preheated barbecue grill, season with 1 tsp salt and grill for 10-15 minutes on each side, turning chicken legs occasionally until cooked through. Meanwhile, prepare piri piri sauce."},{"content":"Place piri piri marinade in mixing bowl and cook <b>7 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Serve chicken legs with piri piri sauce and pickled curry beans."}],"hintsAndTricks":["In South Africa, pickled curry beans are called Kerrie-boontji. It is a very traditional dish, served with a variety of foods.","The pickled curry beans can be prepared up to <b>1 week<b> ahead, and served cold as a salad side dish with your barbecue."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","3h","4 portions"]}